reviewText: It's a pretty good DVD. The first time I viewed it, didn't make as much sense as viewing it after I had some ANMA Japanese Massage training. Note: the pictures on the cover depict techniques covering the neck and shoulders. I would like to see those, but it is not what you get. This DVD covers techniques starting on the back and finishing at the feet.
Excellent DVD.  Very well explained and easy to follow.  However, one might need to have basic knowledge of Tui Na Massage in order to truly understand it.
